<br>
<br>
I have been accused of being a fanboi countless times on tazoon.com boards, and i have tried to AGGRESSIVELY defend this game from the naysayer folk on horizonsvault boards. Sadly as of today 3rd December, I have to say that the beta has been a failure for the %90 of the population that it hosted. Of course, i have seen the non-constructive, non-caring, destructive attacks of many, which led me into my &quot;fanboi&quot; status, but i can tell you this that i have seen more &quot;caring, hard working to make this game better&quot; kind of people saying their goodbye's on tazoon.com <br>
<br>
If the game is released just like it is in beta, it is doomed to fail. Many core ideas behind its system are untested, unfinished or flawed. Even the &quot;no usable loot&quot; system that i have defended at least in 20 different posts on horizonsvault has shown its true face to me, now that the crafters can get their techniqes and formulas by tasking. Do not fall into that trap of &quot;if you want a sword crafted for you, you go kill monsters which give you the resources and formula for it, and you take it to a crafter to get your sword crafted&quot; non-sense anymore. You dont know which mob has the sword formula, and the mob is NOT going to drop metal ore all the time. Its going to deposit flax, crystals, wood, orb essences, slate and all kinds of other stuff which is NOT going to contribute towards your sword. You will end up paying to the crafter in terms of copper/silver and get your item crafted, instead of waiting patiently for a mob to drop 95 copper ore for you to get that sword constructed. <br>
<br>
It is a failure in the roleplayer adventurer's perspective too, multiclassing having nearly no penalty at all, other than the time invested. We will see a lot of lvl 90 warrior/lvl 80 cleric/lvl 80 mage's around. These guys may not have the insta heal or the group heal of a cleric, but they will have access to a very high level heal and very high level buffs, which will negate the use of another cleric in the group. Some people are okay with this and they have valid arguments, but in my eyes this system will be abused resulting in powergamers having access to uber classes, with warrior abilities and self damage buffs, firebolts, leeches, roots, heals and buffs all in one... <br>
<br>
The biggest blow us beta testers took was the untested content. We never battled withered aegis. We never tested dragon flight. We never made a bridge together. We dont know if all those supposedly CONFIRMED things will be in the game. We dont know if mobs will be able to pass through walls of the castles, since we never tested one. With this many things untested by beta community, a lot of questionmarks pop in our minds. <br>
<br>
No matter how many optimizations they have done, we STILL had that incredible amount of memleak and lag at the final event, which was another blow on my hopes. <br>
<br>
But there is still hope for this game. Most of you reading this article will not like or buy this game because they are turned off by some of the core ideas behind the game's mechanics. Some of you refuse to play a game with rock paper scissor combat and i respect that. Some of you want to be able to pick up the sword of the mob that you just killed, and i also respect that. <br>
<br>
If you ask me one thing that should be at release, if this game wants to survive, there is no other choice but the dynamic-intelligent-always on the move Withered Aegist to be present at release. Currently there is no &quot;driving force&quot;, no &quot;aim&quot; in the game other than freeing the subjugated races, which as you know, is a ONE TIME event. They have to do anything and everything possible to make sure that the smart Withered Aegis attacking towns, invading places, forming new blightstorms will be WORKING AT RELEASE. Because fighting off the WA that is attacking us, will be the aim and the reason of playing this game. There is no pvp at end game. There is no legion to be killed by a 80 people raid. The game needs one thing to survive, and thats the promised Withered Aegis. <br>
<br>
The full (long!) review by her:<br>
<br>
