Here is another exert from that same review...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>18. DAY OF A CRAFTER <br>
==================== <br>
<br>
Now, i will write about my experience as a weaponsmith just to give you an idea how a day of a crafter passes in the world of Istaria. <br>
<br>
I log on and find myself near the town shrine. I immediately check my backpack for the situation of money, yay! I had 2 silvers last night but today i have over 9, that means the mining picks that i placed on the consigners sold well! I immediately run to my vault and put about 15 mining picks(with some mining enchantments on them) in my backpack. <br>
<br>
I head out to the consigners, and filter everything else and check the prices on mining picks. Hmm, these guys are selling standard non-magical picks for 300 copper and above. I will place my mining picks with +5mining enchantment on them for the same price, and people will by mine instead of those *evil grin*. I put 4 picks on the consigner in New Trismus(since 1 spell formula that i placed still didnt sell, i might be asking too much but we will see) then I run to 8-9 other towns to check all consigners. I spend about 30 minutes placing 12 more mining picks on sale, and place the rest in my vault. <br>
<br>
I take my brand new deluxe cargo disk and put it in my back back. Checking that i have my smelter, my own pick and smithing hammer, I port to Aughundel, the city of dwarves. I follow the path towards the mines and i follow the rail tracks up into the top of the mountain, where there is a huge refinary. I go back down the ramp and place my cargo disk somewhere reasonable between the refinery and the ore veins. Then I take out my mining pick and start mining the ore. I delete all the extra salt i mine during this process, and i smile when i see &quot;You have mined 10 extra copper ore!&quot; message. I notice the saris guy mining from the same vein I am mining from, I think is this guy a resource stealer? then i see his message that he is sorry and he didnt see me because of lag. I fill my backpack with ore, head back to the cargo disk and empty my ore into it. Luckily a guildy tinkerer finished my cargo armor and instead of doing 10 runs to the cargo disk, i only do 4 runs to it and fill it up with ore. Then i start pulling the cargo disk at %10 of my normal speed which hurts. After about 3 mins of climbing i am on top of the mountain where the refinery is. I have enough ore to make 10 bronze mining picks, but ack! I forgot the dim essences.. I park my cargo disk near the refinery, and i recall. I go check the prices on consigners for the dim essence orbs, and i see that there is none below 45c each. I check my friends list and YAY my dim essence collector friend is online. After messaging him, we meet in Kion Vaultroom and he sells me 40 orbs for 20c each. I go back to Aughundel and back to the refinery. <br>
<br>
First from the raw copper ore, I make 140 bronze bars. The requirement for constructing a mining pick dropped from 8bar to 7 bar today, since i gained a lvl last night before i logged off. I open the create mining pick formula window. I place my dim essence orbs and choose technique for &quot;Mining II&quot; which is +5 to mining skill. I choose 20 picks with %100 success, and i click on construct. Viola! 20 brand new Mining Picks of Mining+5. I recall and deposit those in my bank and then i ask on /gu if any of my guildies need one. I find out that 3-4 people are actually using standard picks and i give them these enchanted ones for free. <br>
<br>
The exp bar moves about %25 but i am still content, since during this period 4 more mining picks sold on consigner. Knowing that by the time i go to class and come back tonight all my new picks will be sold, I log of happily. <br>
<br>
<br>
19. DAY OF AN ADVENTURER <br>
======================== <br>
<br>
And finally ,day of an adventurer, a reaver who just joined the school is out hunting. <br>
<br>
I log on and go to the Reaver Trainer in Kirasanct. I tell him that I want to join the reaver school. &quot;Congradulations! You have just joined among the ranks of the Paladin!&quot; he says. I laugh, another bug. <br>
<br>
Since i leveled my warrior to lvl 22 instead of the required 20 to get iron armor skill, I am quite excited now. I check my guildies list to see if our guild armor crafter is online. He is online but needs some time to craft my iron armor. I gained a new ability called Ethereal blade so i go out to test it. <br>
<br>
I port to Kion and start following the coastline. A mage nearby gives me ice damage effect on my 2 handed sword and I thank her. On my way towards the lvl 18 zombie stonhedge, I see a lvl 25 mob named Master Elethra with 3-4 minion skeletons. By the time I tell myself, &quot;sweet!&quot; she attacks a group of lvl 12's and kills 3 of them. With all the heroic feelings inside me i charge. I use the new ethereal blade ability on the mob and now for 1 minute, i ignore his armor rating. I hit him about %30 more than normal but with his mages casting engulf on me and his clerics healin him, I have no chance. I try to turn around and run, but i get pinioed by one of the archer minions. Then the mage casts grasping ice on me which roots me to ground. Following fireblast kills me and i am just absolutely amazed by how brutal these things are. <br>
<br>
I recall and go back to Kion, I buy some beef stew and soups to lower my death point. I go back to the kion coastline and finally reach the Stonehedge area with the mobs i want. I pull with my spirit bolt now instead of the xbow(which is a pain to change and uses up space on hotbar) and i have quite little downtime with my health leech spells. I find myself using my ehtreal blade on cleric mobs most, since they insta heal themselves and keep healing during battle. With that extra %30 damage, they are no problem. After about 30 minutes of hunting zombies, i get a tell from a random person. He says they have a group and they want to kill some fire golems, but they are lacking a tank. <br>
<br>
I go to the meeting point and we start climbing a mountain, killing lvl 25ish skeletons and zombies on the way. There are clerics and mages in the group, and 1 monk. I lost my defend ability by joining the reaver school so i cannot help them against adds. The mages outdamage me and die often. But luckily we have rezzers and they just rez them. We reach the mountaintop and we enter a lava mountain area. The fire golems are lvl 45, and we have about 6 lvl 20-25 people in group. We are not sure if we can hunt them. At this moment we see an overpowered insta healin self buffin lvl 34 paladin taking on the fire golems with the aid of a lvl 20 spirits. We laugh at the side and tell each other some paladin jokes. <br>
<br>
Then the moment comes, a HUGE fire golem pops near us, size of a 4 story apartment. I ask if the group is ready, and I pull the creature with my spirit bolt. He does about %40 of my total hps worth of damage with each swing. The clerics are doing their jobs though and i am alive, dishing out damage with my etheral blade. Then i realise one mage scream. <br>
<br>
&quot;ITS NOT WORKING! MY FLAME SPELLS ARE NOT WORKING ON HIM, AND I ONLY HAVE 2 ICE SPELLS WHICH ARE ROOT AND EVADE DEBUFF.&quot; <br>
<br>
The other mage casts his fire spells and the first mage was true, the firegolem is not hurt by fire spells. <br>
<br>
The mages are supposed to be the main damage dealers so we have a problem here. I tell everyone to run and i hit the recall button. With server lag and clerics not healin anymore, i simply die to the fire golem. They come back and rez me, and for the rest of the night we kill iron/slate/silver golems, which do take dmg from our mages. We collect TONS of formulas and high level techniques. After about 2 hours of hunting i level and recieve a new ability. I thank the group and recall. I visit the consginers and place the new formulas and techniques i found for sale. <br>
<br>
With enough luck and some rich crafters, tomorrow morning i will be a rich adventurer in iron scalemail <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
